Job Description
Job Purpose
You will be part of the Group Data Management & Governance Office, specifically in the area of Enterprise Data Governance.
You will be leading a team of data governance officers to protect the privacy of all individuals and enhance the value of our data asset. You will have to design and establish data governance programs and initiatives to steer, drive the organization towards data driven, and enable innovations while preserving the confidentiality of data.
The Job
Partner with senior management team, business leaders and technology department to develop and drive an enterprise-wide Data Governance strategy, operationalize the data management policies, procedures and standards;
Be a strong liaison between Business and Technology to ensure that business data related controls are clearly defined, communicated and considered during project / initiatives?? planning and development;
Steer the BU & SU to achieve their goals in a compliance, effective and efficient manner using data and technology;
Strategize to shift mindset and embed data obligations and accountabilities into everyone??s day to day activities, and to develop self-service data culture to improve overall business efficiency;
Design and lead the team to implement data governance programs and initiatives to ensure compliance with regulations, raise the value of data and enable data democratization;
Perform oversight on all data governance programs and initiatives to ensure alignment and effective implementation across the Group;
Lead the secretariat team to support Data Governance Committee and Data Governance Working Group;
Design and implement programs and initiatives to raise the overall data literacy and data control obligations across the Group to enable intelligent workforce and minimize data incidents;
Design, develop and maintain all data governance artefacts (e.g. framework, policies, standards and guidelines) to ensure compliance with regulations, relevancy and up-to-date to meet the organization??s strategic objectives and business needs;
Maintain awareness of industry trends on regulatory compliance, emerging threats and appropriate steps to mitigate the risks;
Highlight any potential concerns/risks and proactively shares best risk management practices;
Take accountability in considering business and regulatory compliance risks and takes appropriate steps to mitigate the risks;
Maintain awareness of industry trends on regulatory compliance, emerging threats and appropriate steps to mitigate the risks;
Highlight any potential concerns/risks and proactively shares best risk management practices; and
Any other ad-hoc duties as assigned.
Degree from recognized tertiary institution with at least 12 years of working experience where at least 5 years of hands-on experience in data governance, data management or compliance in insurance or financial services industry;
Extensive change management skills and experience in managing organization transformation programs;
Excellent interpersonal and communication skills, with ability to manage different levels of stakeholders across the organization and navigate through conflicts and differences competently and with ease;
